<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dismay2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dismay,</orth> vb. 1) tr. to fill with fear and apprehension: <cit><quote>she shall not d. me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.4.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 4, 27</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed not this our captains?</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.2.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 2, 33</bibl></cit>. Partic. <cit><quote>--ed:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 896" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 896</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. luc 273" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 273</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.147" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 147</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.4.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 4, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.570" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 570</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 5.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.3.73" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.174" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.6.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 6, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.269" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 269</bibl>.<lb />2) intr. to take fright: <cit><quote>d. not, princes, at this accident,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 3, 1</bibl></cit>.
